12/11/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic paid a one-day visit to Bulgaria on Thursday (11 November) at the invitation of counterpart Georgi Parvanov.
They discussed bilateral co-operation and regional issues.
In addition, the two heads of state agreed to send a joint letter to Brussels requesting financing for the Sofia-Nis highway project.
In other news Thursday, Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica met with Kosovo Serb representatives to discuss the situation in Kosovo.
According to Belgrade sources, the representatives agreed to back Belgrade's position on Kosovo.
(Sega, 24 Chasa - 12/11/04;
B92 - 11/11/04)
